description.narrative:
The Ministry of Foreign Affairs, through its policy framework, clearly articulated the overarching policy principle of
Leading from the South as enhancing capabilities of CSOs to fulfil lobbying and advocacy with the
following three goals: 1. Prevention and elimination of sexual and gender-based violence against women and girls;
2. Strengthening women’s leadership and women’s participation in (political) decision-making;
3. Strengthening women’s economic empowerment and improving the economic climate for
women.
